Here is a simple C++ program that reads a text file line by line and counts the number of occurrences of a specific word in the file:
```
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <string>

using namespace std;

int main()
{
    // Open the file for reading
    ifstream file("filename.txt");

    // Variable to store the number of occurrences
    int count = 0;

    // Variable to store the word to search for
    string word = "Search";

    // Read the file line by line
    string line;
    while (getline(file, line))
    {
        // Check if the word is found in the current line
        if (line.find(word)!= string::npos)
        {
            count++;
        }
    }

    // Close the file
    file.close();

    // Print the number of occurrences
    cout << "The word " << word << " appears " << count << " times in the file." << endl;

    return 0;
}
```
To use this program, replace "filename.txt" with the name of the text file you want to read, and replace "Search" with the word you want to search for. When you run the program, it will read the file line by line and count the number of times the specified word appears in the file. It will then print the result to the console.

